5.Remove duplicates.

If the interviewer gives an unsorted array, they usually expect the dictionary/set approach.
If they specifically say the array is sorted, they usually expect the two-pointer approach because 
it uses constant extra space.

1st approach-->
l=[2,7,8,9,3,2,7]
n=len(l)

seen={}               <-----
result=[]
for num in l:
    if num not in seen:
        seen[num]=1    <-----
        result.append(num)
print(result)
tc=O(n)
sc=O(n)



2nd approach-->
can make use of set

seen=set()              <----
result=[]
for num in l:
    if num not in seen:
        seen.add=num    <----
        result.append(num)
print(result)
tc=O(n)
sc=O(n)
